T4F Data NoSql Hadoop Server
============================

Shows how to start a HBase Server from the JAVA code.

Build HBase from Source
-----------------------
mvn clean package assembly:assembly help:active-profiles -DskipTests -Dhadoop.profile=2.0

source jdk6.sh
mvn clean package assembly:assembly help:active-profiles -DskipTests -Dhadoop.profile=3.0 -o
rm -fr /w/opt/hbase-0.95-SNAPSHOT
cp target/hbase-0.95-SNAPSHOT.tar.gz /w/opt
cd /w/opt
tar xvfz hbase-0.95-SNAPSHOT.tar.gz
rm hbase-0.95-SNAPSHOT.tar.gz
cd hbase-0.95-SNAPSHOT
cp /t/t4f-data.git/nosql/hbase/common/src/main/resources/hbase-site.xml conf/
cd bin
./start-hbase.sh 
./hbase shell
help
create 'test', 'cf'
list 'test'
put 'test', 'row1', 'cf:a', 'value1'
put 'test', 'row2', 'cf:b', 'value2'
put 'test', 'row3', 'cf:c', 'value3'
scan 'test'
get 'test', 'row1'
disable 'test'
drop 'test'
exit
./stop-hbase.sh

Build HBase with Hadoop 3.0
---------------------------
mvn package assembly:assembly -DskipTests -Dhadoop.profile=3.0
Also works with m2eclipse. Import with profile='!hadoop-1.0, hadoop-3.0'

Manage HBase
------------
60010 HMaster web-interface
60030 RegionServer web-interface

Build HBase Documentation
-------------------------
mvn site
mvn docbkx-maven-plugin:generate-html

HBase Data Model
----------------
key for time series <userid % const><reverse ts><userid>
